<BR><BR>

Ants are not a common clan animal, but there are some southwestern tribes with Ant Clans,
including the Hopi, Pueblo, and Akimel O'odham (Pima) tribes. Ant groupings were particularly 
important among the Pimas, where the people of every Pima village used to be divided into one 
Red Ant Clan and one White Ant Clan. The Cherokee also have an Ant Dance 
among their tribal dance traditions.

