<H2><U>
Native American Legends About Ants
</u></H2>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"  ALT="*"><b><A HREF="
http://www.firstpeople.us/FP-Html-Legends/TheEndoftheFirstWorld-Hopi.html
">The End of the First World</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Hopi Indian myths about the World Fire, including the story of how the survivors took shelter with the Ant People.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"  ALT="*"><b><A HREF="
http://coyotecooks.wordpress.com/2009/12/26/american-indian-storytelling-how-daylight-came-to-be-ant-and-bear/
">How Daylight Came To Be: Ant and Bear</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Salishan Indian legend about how Ant Woman won daytime from the Creator.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"  ALT="*"><b><A HREF="
http://www2.gnb.ca/content/gnb/en/departments/aboriginal_affairs/wolastoqiyik/storytelling.html
">The Ant Story-Teller</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
A short, humorous Native American folktale about Ant's brief career as a storyteller.
<BR>

<H2><U>
Recommended Books of Ant Stories from Native American Myth and Legend
</u><BR><font size=2>Our organization earns a commission from any book bought through these links</font>
</u></H2>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0060203463/natilangofthe-20
">Rat Is Dead And Ant Is Sad</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Picture book illustrating a Pueblo Indian legend about how rumors can spread.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0595150179/natilangofthe-20
">Insect Mythology</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Interesting book on the role of ants and other insects in world mythology, including Native North America and Mesoamerica.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0452276500/natilangofthe-20
">Spirits of the Earth: A Guide to Native American Nature Symbols, Stories, and Ceremonies</A></B>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Book by a Karuk elder about the meanings of Indian animal spirits, including a chapter on ants.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/1555911277/natilangofthe-20
">Native American Animal Stories</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
A great children's collection of American Indian tales about animals, told by Abenaki storyteller Joseph Bruchac. 
<BR>




